properties.description: Maximum time the response should be cached, in seconds if no duration suffix is not specified.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.cache.cachecontrol.must-revalidate
properties.description: Indicate that once it has become stale, a cache must not use the response without re-validating it with the server.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.cache.cachecontrol.no-cache
properties.description: Indicate that the cached response can be reused only if re-validated with the server.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.cache.cachecontrol.no-store
properties.description: Indicate to not cache the response in any case.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.cache.cachecontrol.no-transform
properties.description: Indicate intermediaries (caches and others) that they should not transform the response content.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.cache.cachecontrol.proxy-revalidate
properties.description: Same meaning as the "must-revalidate" directive, except that it does not apply to private caches.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.cache.cachecontrol.s-max-age
properties.description: Maximum time the response should be cached by shared caches, in seconds if no duration suffix is not specified.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.cache.cachecontrol.stale-if-error
properties.description: Maximum time the response may be used when errors are encountered, in seconds if no duration suffix is not specified.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.cache.cachecontrol.stale-while-revalidate
properties.description: Maximum time the response can be served after it becomes stale, in seconds if no duration suffix is not specified.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.cache.period
properties.description: Cache period for the resources served by the resource handler. If a duration suffix is not specified, seconds will be used. Can be overridden by the 'spring.web.resources.cache.cachecontrol' properties.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.cache.use-last-modified
properties.description: Whether we should use the "lastModified" metadata of the files in HTTP caching headers.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.chain.cache
properties.description: Whether to enable caching in the Resource chain.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.chain.compressed
properties.description: Whether to enable resolution of already compressed resources (gzip, brotli). Checks for a resource name with the '.gz' or '.br' file extensions.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.chain.enabled
properties.description: Whether to enable the Spring Resource Handling chain. By default, disabled unless at least one strategy has been enabled.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.chain.strategy.content.enabled
properties.description: Whether to enable the content Version Strategy.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.chain.strategy.content.paths
properties.description: Comma-separated list of patterns to apply to the content Version Strategy.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.chain.strategy.fixed.enabled
properties.description: Whether to enable the fixed Version Strategy.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.chain.strategy.fixed.paths
properties.description: Comma-separated list of patterns to apply to the fixed Version Strategy.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.chain.strategy.fixed.version
properties.description: Version string to use for the fixed Version Strategy.

properties.name: spring.web.resources.static-locations
properties.description: Locations of static resources. Defaults to classpath:[/META-INF/resources/, /resources/, /static/, /public/].

properties.name: spring.webflux.base-path
properties.description: Base path for all web handlers.

properties.name: spring.webflux.format.date
properties.description: Date format to use, for example 'dd/MM/yyyy'.

properties.name: spring.webflux.format.date-time
properties.description: Date-time format to use, for example 'yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss'.

properties.name: spring.webflux.format.time
properties.description: Time format to use, for example 'HH:mm:ss'.

properties.name: spring.webflux.hiddenmethod.filter.enabled
properties.description: Whether to enable Spring's HiddenHttpMethodFilter.

properties.name: spring.webflux.multipart.file-storage-directory
properties.description: Directory used to store file parts larger than 'maxInMemorySize'. Default is a directory named 'spring-multipart' created under the system temporary directory. Ignored when using the PartEvent streaming support.

properties.name: spring.webflux.multipart.headers-charset
properties.description: Character set used to decode headers.

properties.name: spring.webflux.multipart.max-disk-usage-per-part
properties.description: Maximum amount of disk space allowed per part. Default is -1 which enforces no limits.

properties.name: spring.webflux.multipart.max-headers-size
properties.description: Maximum amount of memory allowed per headers section of each part. Set to -1 to enforce no limits.

properties.name: spring.webflux.multipart.max-in-memory-size
properties.description: Maximum amount of memory allowed per part before it's written to disk. Set to -1 to store all contents in memory.

properties.name: spring.webflux.multipart.max-parts
properties.description: Maximum number of parts allowed in a given multipart request. Default is -1 which enforces no limits.

properties.name: spring.webflux.problemdetails.enabled
properties.description: Whether RFC 7807 Problem Details support should be enabled.

properties.name: spring.webflux.static-path-pattern
properties.description: Path pattern used for static resources.

properties.name: spring.webflux.webjars-path-pattern
properties.description: Path pattern used for WebJar assets.

properties.name: spring.webservices.path
properties.description: Path that serves as the base URI for the services.

properties.name: spring.webservices.servlet.init
properties.description: Servlet init parameters to pass to Spring Web Services.

properties.name: spring.webservices.servlet.load-on-startup
properties.description: Load on startup priority of the Spring Web Services servlet.

properties.name: spring.webservices.wsdl-locations
properties.description: Comma-separated list of locations of WSDLs and accompanying XSDs to be exposed as beans.

properties.name: trace
properties.description: Enable trace logs.
